<doc id="91469" wikidata="Q484570" url="?curid=91469" title="Red River County, Texas">
<text>Red River County is a county in the U.S. state of Texas. As of the 2020 census, its population was 11,587. Its county seat is Clarksville. The county was created in 1835 and organized in 1837. It is named for the Red River, which forms its northern boundary. Red River County was the birthplace of John Nance Garner, 32nd Vice President of the United States.

==Geography==
According to the U.S. Census Bureau, the county has a total area of , of which is land and (1.9%) is water.

===Rivers and Lakes===
* Sulphur River
* Red River of the South
* Shawnee Creek (Texas)
* Brevelle Lake

===Major highways===
* U.S. Highway 82
* U.S. Highway 271
* State Highway 37

===Adjacent counties===

* McCurtain County, Oklahoma (north)
* Bowie County (east)
* Morris County (southeast)
* Titus County (south)
* Franklin County (southwest)
* Delta County (southwest)
* Lamar County (west)
* Choctaw County, Oklahoma (northwest)
